<h2 class="h2" style="margin: 0px;">Our Business</h2>
<p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px 0px;">
Global Wealth & Investment Management provides comprehensive banking and investment services tailored to meet the changing wealth-management goals of more than three million individual and institutional customers. Clients have access to services offered through three primary businesses:
</p>


<p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px 0px;"><b>Premier Banking & Investments<span style="font-size: 0.6em; position: relative; top: -0.6em;">TM</span></b> - delivers tailored banking and investment solutions and personalized, priority service to affluent clients, those with investable assets and a mortgage that exceeds $500,000 and those with at least $100,000 of investable assets, through locally based client teams. PB&I offers a full-service and online brokerage, and nearly 4,400 client advisors.
</p>

<p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px 0px;"><b>U.S. Trust, Bank of America Private Wealth Management</b> - provides integrated wealth-management solutions to high-net-worth individuals, middle-market institutions and charitable organizations with investable assets greater than $3 million. More wealthy individuals and families have chosen U.S. Trust to provide personal trust and wealth-management solutions than any other institution (according to VIP Forum, 2006).
</p>

<p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px 0px;"><b>Columbia Management</b> - serves as Bank of America's asset management organization, providing solutions to institutional clients and individual investors. These include separately managed accounts, liquidity strategies, and mutual funds across a variety of investment disciplines within equities, fixed income (taxable and nontaxable) and cash (taxable and nontaxable). As of December 31, 2006, Columbia Management and its affiliates managed assets of $542.9 billion.
</p>

<h2 class="h2" style="margin: 0px;">Overview</h2>
<p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px 0px;">
The Trust Officer provides trust expertise to meet the needs of clients in support of the integrated delivery of products and services and works closely with other team members to define client requirements including legal and tax issues, coordinating service fulfillment and expanding relationships. Additionally, The Trust Officer:
</p>
<ul>
	<li>Provides assistance and technical guidance in the sales and retention process to various team members</li>
	<li>Provides clients with expert knowledge of products and related regulatory requirements</li>
	<li>Participates in the Integrated Advice Sales Process as part of the client team as the expert in trust solutions</li>
	<li>Supports team profitability by focusing on achieving standard pricing for new and existing fiduciary accounts</li>
	<li>Understands, and works to achieve the financial, retirement and estate planning goals of the client</li>
	<li>Responds to clients' fiduciary inquiries and communications independently or in conjunction with the U.S. Trust, Bank of America Private Wealth Management Sales and Service team</li>
	<li>Sets and monitors proactive client contact standards for assigned fiduciary/trust relationships</li>
	<li>Understands and follows the terms of fiduciary/trust agreements</li>
	<li>Maintains accountability for risk management reporting, including exceptions</li>
</ul>

<h2 class="h2" style="margin: 0px;">Qualifications</h2>
<ul>
	<li>Masters of Business Administration and/or joint Masters of Business and Law degrees</li>
	<li>Proven record of academic success, accompanied by exceptional communication, critical thinking and relationship building skills</li>
	<li>Strong business acumen, and the ability to build rapport and trust with clients and colleagues</li>
	<li>Ability to fully understand document provision, trust and estate law, taxes, investments and the legal framework of trust administration and follow the terms of governing documents</li>
</ul>

<h2 class="h2" style="margin: 0px;">Training</h2>
<p style="margin: 0px 0px 12px 0px;">
New hires will undergo a formal training process that begins with a multi-module training program designed to educate them on our product offerings as well as preparation for necessary licensing. The program is also designed to integrate new hires into the Bank of America Community via structured coaching, networking events and exposure to senior leaders.
</p>

